zaar on Erollisi Marr</span><hr size=1> A tinkering bazaar will be held on Erollisi Marr and attended to by gnomish tinkerers of various experience levels at the third windmill (with Bom Knotwood) in Steamfont Mountains from 6PM to midnight Pacific USA time on Friday 14 December. <br>
This event will be mutually beneficial, because prices will be set no higher than twice the cost to make while the tinkerer gains experience. The success rate to make for a tinkerer not at a trivial level for a next higher gadget is about 50% - hence, twice the price. <br>
<br>
Please take a moment to look at the items and prices for tinkered contraptions at the Tinkering Compendium at www.eqportal.com/tinkering. You may find something you've always been looking for this holiday season. <br>
<br>
This is a great time to come out and support your tinkerers on Erollisi Marr and hire one or two to make newly discovered Luclin items: The event will improve the tinkerers experience making Luclin items with less failure. Rebreathers and aqualungs will be some of the featured gadgets available. <br>
<br>
A master fletcher is requested to support by making as many shaped ashwood recurve bows as possible - you will be reimbursed 40PP for each bow by the respective tinkerer needing them for catapults. <br>
<br>
Whether a simple fishing pole or a spyglass is your desire, your patronage is appreciated. Again, join in this tinkering station event and find out who some of the tinkerers are on our server. Be safe and see you there. <br>
